    <command:details>
      <command:name>Invoke-CpmfUipsCLI</command:name>
      <command:verb>Invoke</command:verb>
      <command:noun>CpmfUipsCLI</command:noun>
      <maml:description>
        <maml:para>Single entry point for the CpmfUipsCLI wrapper. Dispatches to CpmfUipsPack public functions.</maml:para>
      </maml:description>
    </command:details>
    <maml:description>
      <maml:para>Invoke-CpmfUipsCLI routes a subcommand string to the corresponding CpmfUipsPack function. All remaining parameters are forwarded via splatting. UIPS_* environment variables are applied as defaults before forwarding, following the same four-layer hierarchy as CpmfUipsPack.</maml:para>
      <maml:para>Subcommands:   pack              Invoke-CpmfUipsPack   install-tool      Install-CpmfUipsPackCommandLineTool   uninstall-tool    Uninstall-CpmfUipsPackCommandLineTool   install-config    Install-CpmfUipsPackConfig   uninstall-config  Uninstall-CpmfUipsPackConfig   install-hook      Install-CpmfUipsPackGitHook   diagnose          Get-CpmfUipsPackDiagnostics</maml:para>
    </maml:description>
